 :tx/rationale "Create task: LIVESTORE-KERNEL: Store::apply_datoms(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) — incremental datom insertion without schema validation. CONTEXT: LiveStore::write_tx needs to apply datoms from a persisted TxFile to the in-memory Store. Transaction::commit() fails for datoms with attributes not yet in the schema (schema bootstrap ordering problem). Store::from_datoms() handles this by processing all datoms holistically, but it's a full rebuild. Store::genesis() already has the correct incremental pattern (lines 958-986): insert into BTreeSet + update entity_index, attribute_index, vaet_index, avet_index, live_view, MaterializedViews. APPROACH: (1) Extract the loop body from Store::genesis() into pub fn apply_datoms(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]). (2) For each datom: insert into self.datoms (BTreeSet), observe_datom for MaterializedViews, update all 5 secondary indexes. (3) After all datoms: rebuild schema from self.datoms via Schema::from_datoms (schema may have new attributes). Update frontier. (4) This method DOES NOT validate against schema — the datoms are from persisted txn files and are already validated. (5) Update Store::genesis() to use apply_datoms internally (DRY). (6) Update load_store incremental path to use apply_datoms instead of Transaction::commit (fixes pre-existing stale-store bug). ACCEPTANCE: (A) apply_datoms on a genesis store with full_schema_datoms produces a store with all schema attributes registered. (B) apply_datoms on a store with schema datoms then observation datoms succeeds (the commit() path fails here). (C) Store::genesis() still produces identical output (refactor, not behavior change). (D) All 1742+ tests pass. (E) load_store incremental path uses apply_datoms and no longer silently returns stale stores. TRACES: INV-STORE-020, ADR-FOUNDATION-034. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs + crates/braid/src/layout.rs + crates/braid/src/live_store.rs"
